10pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.34pt; padding-left:4.66pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">We</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> do not believe that it is necessary to develop a new standard form</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> for reporting</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> but</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">this is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">on the understanding that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> all the required information is captured</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> in the report.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> We do however believe that medical examinations need to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> be comprehensive and perhaps </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">include as a matter of course certain agreed methods of objective testing, for example Waddell’s test.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.34pt; padding-left:4.66pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">We believe that the accreditation system should also deal with claims for psychological and psychiatric injury in low </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">value RTA cases.  This type of claim is becoming increasingly widespread and would benefit from a similar level of scrutiny as is currently been suggested for whiplash claims.  It is also an area that is prone to fraud and exaggeration and is equally diffi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">cult to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">validate</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> objectively</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.34pt; padding-left:4.66pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">It is essential that the scope of the accre</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ditation scheme includes the setting of prices</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> for medical reports</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">We</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> feel that work on pricing should start </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">immediately</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> and that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">fee</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">s should be fixed.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">As things stand</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> there is n</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> mandatory</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> standard pricing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> structure</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">for the costs of medical reports</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">The Civil Procedure Rule Committee felt that it should not set rates for medical reports and invited the MoJ to look at pricing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, with a view to reducing the costs of litigation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.  In </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">our</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> view that was an opportunity lost.  N</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">evertheless, the MoJ should </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">look at</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> pricing now.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">  The introduction of fixed fees would lead to a reduction in costs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, bring consistency and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> see</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> an end to dispute</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> in individual cases.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.34pt; padding-left:4.66pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">It has taken some time for this</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> stage to be reached</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> but now that there is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">large </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">amount of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">consensus, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">w</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> are keen to see the introduction of a timetable for delivery of the accreditation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">scheme, so as to ensure </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">implementation of the reforms at the earliest opportunity.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Further</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> possib</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">le areas of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> reform</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> – awards for PSLA and inducements</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Year on year, damages </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">for PSLA </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">in low value whiplash claims have risen and will continue to do so</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> if the current system continues</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">We</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> believe that the cost of whiplash claims is now such that considera</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">tion should be given to hold award levels </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">at present levels </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">for the foreseeable future</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.  Whilst this would need judicial consideration,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> we believe it would assist if the committee were to look at this area.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">The ban on offering immediate inducement</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">s for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> br</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">inging a claim</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> should </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">be extended</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> to law firms.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">A ban on the practice is already in place for CMCs and extending the ban would </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">eradicate</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> the practice altogether. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">This would assist</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> further</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> in combatting fraud and wo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">uld </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">support</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">proposed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">reforms in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">w</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">hiplash</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> arena</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">F</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">raud in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">personal injury</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> claims</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> – Law Commission</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">The committee noted that fraud is a serious issue and one that impacts upon claims for whiplash.  The law is not as effective as it should be in tackling fraud and does not provide a suffici</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ent deterrent effect.  The committee will be aware that the Law Commission suggested fraud in personal injury claims as one of the topics for inclusion in its 12</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Programme of reform.  DWF was one of the 16 respondees who agreed that the topic should be i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ncluded in the 12</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Programme.  The issue of fraud is one that needs to be addressed, which would in turn increase the impact of reforms in claims for whiplash.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">We are aware that the issue of fraud was suggested for inclusion in the Law Commission’s 11</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Programme of refo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">rm.  At that time the MO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">J did not feel that there was sufficient support for change in the law and the Law Commission would not consider the matter at that stage.  Since then, our view is that fraud has become a more significant issue for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> the insurance industry and for the wider public.  In our view there is now widespread support for reform in th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">is area and we would urge the MO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">J to endorse the need for reform in this area and see it as worthy of the Law Commission’s consideration.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:15pt; margin:0pt 0pt 9pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_GoBack"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></a></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>